# Comments should explain "why", not "what"

Comments should never tell what is happening, but only be used to explain why something is done.

## ❌ Don't

```dart
// This function validates the user email
bool validateEmail(String email) {
  // Check if email contains @ symbol
  return email.contains('@');
}
```

## ✅ Do

```dart
// Email validation is simplified since we only need basic format checking
// for the prototype phase
bool validateEmail(String email) {
  return email.contains('@');
}
```

# Private methods should be sorted below public methods

All private methods (prefixed with `_` in Dart) should be sorted below any public methods in the class.

## ❌ Don't

```dart
class UserService {
  void _privateHelperMethod() {
    // Implementation
  }

  void publicMethod() {
    // Implementation
  }
}
```

## ✅ Do

```dart
class UserService {
  void publicMethod() {
    // Implementation
  }

  void _privateHelperMethod() {
    // Implementation
  }
}
``` 